    {
      "@id": "urn:pharmagent:mpoc-boite-a-outil:excerpt:022",
      "@type": "pharm:SourceExcerpt",
      "name": "MPOC-boite-a-outil - extrait 22",
      "description": "## Boîte à outils - MPOC ## Gaz à effet de serre et les pompes HFA Tennison, Imogen et al. Health care's response to climate change: a carbon footprint assessment of the NHS in England. The Lancet Planetary Health, Volume 5, Issue 2, e84 - e92. Disponible : [https://www.thelancet.com/action/showCitFormats?doi=10.1016%2FS2542-5196%2820%2930271-0&amp;pii=S 2542-5196%2820%2930271-0](https://www.thelancet.com/action/showCitFormats?doi=10.1016%2FS2542-5196%2820%2930271-0&pii=S2542-5196%2820%2930271-0) Fidler L, Green S, Wintemute K. Les aérosols-doseurs pressurisés et leurs répercussions sur les changements climatiques. CMAJ 2022 March 28;194:E460. doi : 10.1503/cmaj.211747-f. Disponible : [https://www.cmaj.ca/content/cmaj/194/23/E830.full.pdf](https://www.cmaj.ca/content/cmaj/194/23/E830.full.pdf) Janson C, Henderson R, Löfdahl M, et al Carbon footprint impact of the choice of inhalers for asthma and COPD Thorax 2020;75:82-84. Disponible: https://thorax.bmj.com/content/75/1/82.citation-tools Cascades Canada : https://cascadescanada.ca/action-areas/pharmacy-and-prescribing/",
      "sourceDocument": {
        "@id": "urn:pharmagent:mpoc-boite-a-outil:doc"
      },
      "sourcePage": "unknown",
      "sourceSection": "Boîte à outils - MPOC",
      "sourceQuote": "## Boîte à outils - MPOC ## Gaz à effet de serre et les pompes HFA Tennison, Imogen et al. Health care's response to climate change: a carbon footprint assessment of the NHS in England. The Lancet Planetary Health, Volume 5, Issue 2, e84 - e92. Disponible : [https://www.thelancet.com/action/showCitFormats?doi=10.1016%2FS2542-5196%2820%2930271-0&amp;pii=S 2542-5196%2820%2930271-0](https://www.thelancet.com/action/showCitFormats?doi=10.1016%2FS2542-5196%2820%2930271-0&pii=S2542-5196%2820%2930271-0) Fidler L, Green S, Wintemute K. Les aérosols-doseurs pressurisés et leurs répercussions sur les changements climatiques. CMAJ 2022 March 28;194:E460. doi : 10.1503/cmaj.211747-f. Disponible : [https://www.cmaj.ca/content/cmaj/194/23/E830.full.pdf](https://www.cmaj.ca/content/cmaj/194/23/E830.full.pdf) Janson C, Henderson R, Löfdahl M, et al Carbon footprint impact of the choice of inhalers for asthma and COPD Thorax 2020;75:82-84. Disponible: https://thorax.bmj.com/content/75/1/82.citation-tools Cascades Canada : https://cascadescanada.ca/action-areas/pharmacy-and-prescribing/",
